        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Cincinnati June 14. 1880.<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd. S. Morais.<lb/>
                Philad&#58;<lb/>
                My valued Friend.<lb/></p>
            <p>I am almost ashamed<lb/> after such a long silence to take my pen<lb/> to indite a few lines to you.  I have&#44; and<lb/> you can certainly have some consolation&#44;<lb/> when I say frankly to you that it<lb/> not alone to you that I have been so<lb/> very negligent but to my nearest and<lb/> dearest relatives and friends&#44; just so<lb/> fond as I formerly was in writing.  I<lb/> now am in the same degree reluc&#45;<lb/>tant to take up my pen and paper&#44;<lb/> probably it may be assigned as a<lb/> cause&#44; the advancement of my age.<lb/>  I hope however that as the spir&#45;<lb/>it moved me this evening&#44; it will<lb/> again exercise its influence on me.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I cheerfully acknowledge the<lb/> receipt of Henry&#39; work.  <sic>Emminent</sic><lb/> Israelites of the 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> century&#44; also<lb/> the &#34;Penn Monthly&#34; containing the<lb/> article from your pen&#39; for which<lb/> please accept thanks.  Would it<lb/> not be well for Henry to send a<lb/> few copies of <hi rend="underline">His</hi> work to Block &#38;<lb/> allowing them the regular per&#45;<lb/>centage off&#44; he can have the<lb/> advantage of a good weekly<lb/> advertisement of it in the &#34;Is&#45;<lb/>raelite and Deborah&#34; without<lb/> costing him any thing.  You<lb/> know advertising is a very<lb/> expensive matter if you have<lb/> to pay for it.  let Him send them<lb/> say a dozen copies&#44; you know<lb/> they are perfectly responsible &#38;<lb/> there can be no better medium<lb/> for heralding the works than the<lb/> Israelites it is read everywhere<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>and probably they might also ad&#45;<lb/>vertise it in the &#34;&#91;&#63;&#93;.&#34;  I<lb/> merely throw out these sugges&#45;<lb/>tions for what they are worth.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dr Wise has lost his mother<lb/> at an advanced age she<lb/> died on Friday and <sic>burried</sic> on<lb/> Sunday in one of our adjoining<lb/> States.  He was not well enough<lb/> to go to the funeral &#91;&#63;&#93;.<lb/></p>
            <p>I hope this will meet you<lb/> dear Nina and all the dear ones<lb/> in health&#44; all well with us here<lb/> thank God.<lb/></p>
            <p>We are on the Eve of a<lb/> Great convention to be held here&#44;<lb/> and Dr Lilienthal&#39;s 25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> anniver&#45;<lb/>sary of his ministry great prepara<lb/>rations are making by his congrega&#45;<lb/>tion to give the event great &#91;&#63;&#93;.<lb/></p>
            <p>Excuse brevity Love from all.<lb/>
                as ever truly.<lb/>
                Jacob Ezekiel<lb/></p>
        </body>
